<#
.SYNOPSIS
    Remediates WN10-CC-000391 DISA STIG for Windows 10.

.DESCRIPTION
    Disables Internet Explorer functionality on Windows 10 systems
    by configuring registry settings that prevent 
    users from launching or using Internet Explorer.

    This strengthens system security by reducing exposure to legacy 
    web technologies, mitigating known vulnerabilities in Internet Explorer,
    and encouraging use of modern, supported browsers.
#>
.NOTES
    Author          : Kevin Mejia
    LinkedIn        :https://www.linkedin.com/in/kevin-mejia-901039270/
    GitHub          : https://github.com/Kevin-M1
    Date Created    : 2025-08-31
    Last Modified   : 2025-08-31
    Version         : 1.0
    CVEs            : N/A
    Plugin IDs      : N/A
    STIG-ID         : WN10-CC-000391

.TESTED ON
    Date(s) Tested  : 
    Tested By       : 
    Systems Tested  : 
    PowerShell Ver. : 

.USAGE
    
    Example syntax:
    PS C:\> .\__(WN10-CC-000391).ps1 

PS C:\Users\Kevin0715> # Define registry path and key
>> $regPath = "HKLM:\SOFTWARE\Policies\Microsoft\Internet Explorer\Main"
>>
>> # Create the registry path if it doesn't exist
>> if (-not (Test-Path $regPath)) {
>>     New-Item -Path $regPath -Force | Out-Null
>> }
>>
>> # Set the policy value: 1 = Disable Internet Explorer 11 as a standalone browser
>> Set-ItemProperty -Path $regPath -Name "DisableIE" -Type DWord -Value 1
>>
>> # Optional: Force group policy to refresh
>> gpupdate /force
>>
>> Write-Output "`n? Internet Explorer 11 has been disabled as a standalone browser."
Updating policy...

Computer Policy update has completed successfully.
